Defendant Gage Steven Masch in court with attorney Marcus J Sengstock.  Defendant Gage Steven Masch in custody.  Erin M. Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State placed negotiations on the record. Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Randolph L. and Sommer S.

As to Count 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve  6 MONTHS at the House of Corrections with 107 days credit.

As to Count 2:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve  9 MONTHS at the House of Corrections with 0 days credit CONCURRENT to Count 3. Straight time. Court will allow for participation in vocational programming.

As to Count 3:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve  9 MONTHS at the House of Corrections with 0 days credit CONCURRENT to Count 2. Straight time. Court will allow for participation in vocational programming.

As to Counts 2 and 3:
Court STAYED the sentences and placed the defendant on 3 YEARS probation.

As a condition of sentencing, the Court will sign an order requiring the defendant to submit to Sexually Transmitted Diseases testing. State to submit a proposed order.

  Conditions of Probation:
- No unsupervised contact with anyone under the age of 18.
- No contact with the victim as specified in the criminal complaint, their school, work, residence, or the victim's parents. This includes electronic communication.
- No accounts on social networking sites, but the Court will allow the defendant to maintain an email account. 
- Any devices with electronic communication capabilities must be made available on demand to the agent for immediate inspection.
- Department of corrections to review the defendant's file and conduct an additional Sex Offender Evaluation and provide appropriate counseling and/or treatment if deemed appropriate.
- Defendant must register as a sex offender for 10 a period of years.
- Provide a DNA sample.

The Court ordered that all court costs, fees, and surcharges (including DNA) be paid from 25% of institution funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition probation.  DOC to collect those sums. Any amount remaining due and owing at the end of probation is subject to civil judgment. Defendant to pay DNA surcharge as to Count 1. Court WAIVED DNA surcharge on Counts 2 and 3 as they are part of a continuous course of conduct.

Defendant to enter into a payment plan with the Department of Corrections.

To each of the counts in the AMENDED INFORMATION:   Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Defendant advised he may have to register as a sex offender.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the AMENDED Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  
Defendant is remanded pending sentencing on 6-3-2015 at 8:30am Branch 25.
